    <stitle>7.3 Liter Diesel Engine Service (1991) - INTRODUCTION - AIR INDUCTION AND EXHAUST SYSTEMS</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>AIR INDUCTION AND EXHAUST SYSTEMS</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="0">
            <title>Description</title>
            <para>The intake and exhaust systems consist of those components that convey filtered air to the engine
                cylinders and the exhaust gases to the atmosphere. The intake system includes an air cleaner, a one
                piece cast aluminum intake manifold and intake valves. The exhaust system includes two cast iron exhaust
                manifolds, muffler and exhaust piping (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk document="e435_12.xml" xrefid="ef435IN19">i.19</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ).
            </para>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
